Using a peak flowmeter, a pulmonary function technologist obtains the following:
The technologist should
A. Conclude that bronchodilatation has occurred.
B. Report the average of the two best efforts.
C. Perform at least one more peak flow trial.
D. Report the patient's peak flow as 750 L/min.
Answer: C

A polarographic oxygen analyzer used to measure expired gas in a metabolic system
should always be calibrated with
A. Gas concentrations higher and lower than the expected measurement
B. Oxygen mixtures containing 4% and 8% carbon dioxide
C. 100% oxygen and 100% nitrogen, fully saturated
D. Air and fully saturated 100% oxygen.

diagnosed as having asthma yield the following results:
Which of the following is the best explanation for these?
A. Condensation of moisture in the peak flowmeter
B. Normal response
C. Improper calibration of the peak flowmeter
D. Increasing airways resistance in the subject
Answer: D
